{"lemma":"رِفْقُ","slug":"رِفْقُ","root":"ر.ف.ق","root_slug":"ر-ف-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ف-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16192","n16200","n16201"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%81%D9%92%D9%82%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be kind, to be nice, to be gentle"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be a companion, to be a friend"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَفَقَ (rafaqa, “to be kind, to be nice”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَفُقَ (rafuqa, “to be kind, to be nice”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَفِقَ (rafiqa, “to be kind, to be nice”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of رِفْقَة (rifqa)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of رُفْقَة (rufqa)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strike (someone's) elbow"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bind (a camel's) arm (to prevent it from moving quickly)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have one's elbow twisted or distorted (of a camel)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16192","headword_ar":"رَفَقَ","root":"rfq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rifoqN","text_ar":"رِفْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O, Mgh, * Msb, * K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marofiqN","text_ar":"مَرْفِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirofaqN","text_ar":"مِرْفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, O, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marofaqN","text_ar":"مَرْفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafiqa","text_ar":"رَفِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, O, K,) [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqN","text_ar":"رَفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafuqa","text_ar":"رَفُقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK, O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, gentle, soft, tender, gracious, courteous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"civil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he be haved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acted, gently, softly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (JK, S, O, Mgh, Msb, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqa bihi","text_ar":"رَفَقَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, S, O, Mgh, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, O, K,) inf. ns. as above; (O, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafiqa","text_ar":"رَفِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafuqa","text_ar":"رَفُقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, gentle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he behaved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acted, gently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, O, Mgh, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, O, K;) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trf~q","text_ar":"ترفّق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Mgh, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Arfqhu","text_ar":"ارفقهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AZ, O, K.) Hence the saying of the Prophet,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano rafaqa biA^um~atiY rafaqa A@ll~`hu bihi","text_ar":"مَنْ رَفَقَ بِاُمَّتِى رَفَقَ ا@للّٰهُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who is gentle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with my people, God will be gentle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) [Hence, also,] one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trf~q","text_ar":"ترفّق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY A^amorihi","text_ar":"فِى اَمْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqa fiyhi","text_ar":"رَفَقَ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is indicated in the O]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He used gentleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acted gently, in his affair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^at~aY","text_ar":"تَاَتَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AtY","text_ar":"اتى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liHaAjatihi","text_ar":"لِحَاجَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trf~q","text_ar":"ترفّق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He applied himself with gentleness to his needful affair"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"business;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^at~aY","text_ar":"تَاَتَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AtY","text_ar":"اتى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liloA^amori","text_ar":"لِلْاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trf~q","text_ar":"ترفّق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He applied himself with gentle ness to the affair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talaT~afa","text_ar":"تَلَطَّفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lTf","text_ar":"لطف"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafuqa","text_ar":"رَفُقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in form like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faruba","text_ar":"فَرُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, gentle, delicate, nice, neat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skilful, in work"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"operation; the contr. of such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axoraq","text_ar":"اَخْرَق"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqotu AlEamala","text_ar":"رَفَقْتُ العَمَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made, the deed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"work, soundly, thoroughly, skilfully, judiciously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqotu fiY Als~ayori","text_ar":"رَفَقْتُ فِى السَّيْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I pro ceeded in a right,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a moderate, manner in journeying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in pace."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)       -A2-  See also 4.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaAqapN","text_ar":"رَفَاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n. signifying The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafayq","text_ar":"رَفَيق"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.) Fr says, I heard a man at 'Arafát saying [to the pilgrims there assembled],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalakumu","text_ar":"جَعَلَكُمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hN fiY rafaAqapi muHam~adK Sal~aY A@ll~`hu Ealayohi wasal~ama","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهٌ فِى رَفَاقَةِ مُحَمَّدٍ صَلَّى ا@للّٰهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God make you to be in the companionship of Mohammad: may God bless and save him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) [And accord. to the TK, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafuqa bihi","text_ar":"رَفُقَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaAqapN","text_ar":"رَفَاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafiyq","text_ar":"رَفِيق"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but what is commonly said in this sense is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAfqahu","text_ar":"رَافقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqa fulaAnFA","text_ar":"رَفَقَ فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He struck the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirofaq","text_ar":"مِرْفَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elbow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqa Aln~aAqapa","text_ar":"رَفَقَ النَّاقَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafoqN","text_ar":"رَفْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bound the she-camel's arm"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"together with the shank"},{"kind":"text","text":"(for such is the common practice)], (S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to prevent her going quickly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,) when fearing her yearning towards, or longing for, her home, or accustomed place: (S, O, K:) [or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqa AlbaEiyra","text_ar":"رَفَقَ البَعِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafoqN","text_ar":"رَفْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bound the camel's neck"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eunuq","text_ar":"عُنُق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[probably, I think, a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDud","text_ar":"عَضُد"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to his pastern,"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of a slight lameness therein. (JK.)       -A5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafiqa","text_ar":"رَفِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a camel, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqN","text_ar":"رَفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had his elbow dis torted from his side."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA and TK. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqN","text_ar":"رَفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arofaqu","text_ar":"اَرْفَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafiqa","text_ar":"دَفِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafiqato","text_ar":"رَفِقَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqN","text_ar":"رَفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is probably said of a she-camel, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She had, in her teat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"teats, what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqN","text_ar":"رَفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see, again, this word below.]"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Mgh","Msb","K","AZ","JK"]},{"entry_id":"n16200","headword_ar":"رِفْقٌ","root":"rfq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqa","text_ar":"رَفَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gentleness, softness, tenderness, graciousness, courteousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"civility; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunofN","text_ar":"عُنْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, Mgh, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luTofN","text_ar":"لُطْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Husonu SaniyEK","text_ar":"حُسْنُ صَنِيعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, O, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liynu jaAnibK","text_ar":"لِينُ جَانِبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laTaAfapu fiEolK","text_ar":"لَطَافَةُ فِعْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafaqN","text_ar":"رَفَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAfiqapN","text_ar":"رَافِقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"likewise; whence the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awolaY","text_ar":"اَوْلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnFA raAfiqapF","text_ar":"فُلَانًا رَافِقَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He treated such a one with gentleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (JK, IDrd, O.) It is also explained as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good submission to that which conduces to what is comely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gentleness, delicacy, nicety, neatness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skilfulness, in work"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"operation; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuroqN","text_ar":"خُرْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing by means of which one seeks help"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assistance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirofaqN","text_ar":"مِرْفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["IDrd","O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n16201","headword_ar":"رَفَقٌ","root":"rfq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafiqa","text_ar":"رَفِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph.       -A2-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Easy of attainment."},{"kind":"text","text":"] You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marotaEN rafaqN","text_ar":"مَرْتَعٌ رَفَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of pasturing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of unrestrained and plentiful pasturing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy to be sought"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and attained"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='N rafaqN","text_ar":"مَا=ءٌ رَفَقٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water that is easy"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be sought"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and taken:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the well-rope is short."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAjapN rafaqu Albigoyapi","text_ar":"حَاجَةٌ رَفَقُ البِغْيَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An object of want that is easy"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be sought and attained"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, K.)       -A3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A distortion of the elbow"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the side."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, O, K. [Said to be the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rafiqa","text_ar":"رَفِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.]) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stoppage of the orifice of the teat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the orifices of the teats,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a she-camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) so says Zeyd Ibn-Kuthweh: (O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a disorder in the orifice of the teat, in consequence of being badly milked, or of the milker's not shaking the teat to remove what remained in it, so that the milk reverts into the udder, and turns to blood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"becomes coagulated and mixed with yellow water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K. [Perhaps in this sense, also, an inf. n.: see 1, last sentence.])       -A4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rufoqapN","text_ar":"رُفْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["JK","S","O","K"]}]}}